OL,3,CGlasgow student took own life after
OL,4,Cbeing falsely told he had failed his
OL,5,Cdegree
OL,7,FThe family say that after Ethan's
OL,8,Fmother sought answers from the
OL,9,Funiversity, an internal investigation
OL,10,Fproduced a report confirming that he
OL,11,Fhad actually been awarded the wrong
OL,12,Fgrade for that course due to an error
OL,13,Fby the university and should have
OL,14,Fgraduated with a 2:1 Honours degree.
OL,16,FThey claim that the error was not
OL,17,Fspotted by any University of Glasgow
OL,18,Fstaff, nor identified by two internal
OL,19,Fexam boards and one external exam
OL,20,Fboard.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
