OL,4,Cbeing falsely told he had failed his
OL,5,Cdegree
OL,7,FSpeaking at a press conference at the
OL,8,Ffamily solicitor's office in Glasgow
OL,9,Fon Tuesday, Ethan's mother said: "My
OL,10,Fson, Ethan, was so happy to be
OL,11,Faccepted to study at the University of
OL,12,FGlasgow. We, as a family, were
OL,13,Fdelighted for him.
OL,15,F"Ethan was a kind, caring young man
OL,16,Fwho was very much loved. So it breaks
OL,17,Fmy heart to now be aware of the mental
OL,18,Fanguish this university must have
OL,19,Fcaused my son.
