OL,3,CGlasgow student took own life after
OL,4,Cbeing falsely told he had failed his
OL,5,Cdegree
OL,7,F"Ethan left this world believing he
OL,8,Fhad failed, and the University of
OL,9,FGlasgow were correct. The truth is,
OL,10,FEthan had successfully attained a 2:1
OL,11,Fhonours degree, despite the university
OL,12,Frepeatedly informing him he had been
OL,13,Funsuccessful.
OL,15,F"They failed him, not only
OL,16,Facademically, but also to support him.
OL,17,FMy son was failed from having a duty
OL,18,Fof care from the educational system,
OL,19,Fresulting in my family having been
OL,20,Frobbed from having Ethan in our lives.
